<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1001,1495]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1001,1028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Aedeagal sheath ventro-apically with a pair of strongly sclerotized postgonites as long as bifurcated processes of aedeagal median rod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1001,1495]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,532,1073,1100]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
Supracervical setae approximately 17. Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme slightly longer than 1/2 basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme. Arista with arb = 5–6/5. Palpus with hollow-shaped sense organ. Cibarial, medial sensilla 8–9 per side; posterior sensilla 5–6 per side. All tarsi with gray tarsomeres IV and V. Aedeagus with free sclerite within outer membrane (ch.59-1).
</paragraph>
