<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1001,1495]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1362,1388]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is closely related to the foregoing species, 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1076,1361,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afoliolata">
<emphasis box="[936,953,1362,1387]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[967,1076,1361,1387]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">afoliolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as having been misidentified to be the latter by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[320,538,1397,1424]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="419 - 429" refId="ref34109" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J. &amp; Gao, J. J. (2005 b) The Phortica (s. str.) foliiseta species-complex (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from China and its adjacent countries. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30, 419 - 429." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[385,433,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. (2005b)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng" box="[661,876,1397,1424]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cheng" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="614 - 632" refId="ref34455" refString="Cheng, Y., Gao, J. J., Watabe, H. &amp; Chen, H. W. (2008) Revision of the genus Phortica Schiner 1862 in China (Diptera: Drosophilidae). Zoological Studies, 47, 614 - 632." type="journal article" year="2008">
Cheng 
<emphasis box="[740,788,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
found two distinct forms included in the 
<typeStatus box="[1329,1436,1398,1424]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,320,1433,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afoliolata">
<emphasis box="[181,198,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[211,320,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">afoliolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described one of them as a new species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[860,1061,1433,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xishuangbanna">
<emphasis box="[860,877,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[890,1061,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">xishuangbanna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species can be clearly distinguished from each other by the diagnoses revised in this study.
</paragraph>
